GateDocument.TextWithNodes: III Workshop on Mobility and Replication Brussels - Belgium , July 20 , 1998 http : / / gsd . di . uminho . pt / wmr 98 / - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Call for Papers The third ECOOP workshop on mobility and replication is focusing on object replication and consistency issues . The workshop will try to build bridges between the database community and the mobile computing community . Many researchers in both communities are working on object replication and consistency issues but the goals are often different . One side is mostly focusing on implementing transactions , recovery , and the ACID properties , whereas the other side is mostly focusing on implementing availability , caching , and user mobility . Topics of interest include , but are not limited to : * Application needs for replication * ACID properties in replicated systems * Distributed transactions * Replication for load distribution * Replication for availability * Replication for fault tolerance * Autonomous creation of replicas * Disconnected operation * Replicated active objects * Update protocols * Release consistency and other consistency models The main goal of the workshop is to get a better understanding of the replication and consistency issues , including the application needs . Interested participants should submit a position paper of at most 4 pages . Papers must be in HTML or plain text and submitted by Email to birger . andersen @ jfu . hs . hr . All accepted papers will be made available at the workshop home page . Submission Details Authors submitting position papers discussing new and untraditional ideas that can fill a part of the gap between the database community and the mobile computing community , and with a good force for starting discussions , may be selected for presentation of their work . Submissions are due to : June 1 , 1998 Notification of acceptance : June 15 , 1998 The result of the evaluation may be : Accepted for presentation , Accepted for participation , Rejected All workshop organizers will review all position papers . Authors of the best papers will be given time for presentations . We will use a couple of hours for group discussions , putting the participants in 3 - 4 discussion groups . To direct the group discussions we will hand out for each group a list of tasks . No submission received after the submission due date will be accepted for presentation . Number of participants is limited to 20 . Participants selected for presentations will be encouraged to bring copies of full papers elaborating on their work . We expect to be able to publish the best papers in the ECOOP'98 Workshop Reader or in a related publication .
